    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "AMERICAN\nOVERSEAS\nMERICAN",
      "AOA-AMERICAN OVERSEAS AIRLINES\nBoeing 377 Stratocruiser\nAOA, a wholly owned\nsubsidiary of American Airlines,\ninaugurated\nStratocruiser service\non its\nNew York-\nLondon\nroute\non\nAugust\nthese\n17th,\n1949,\nwith\ntwo\nof\naircraft. One of these, named\nGreat Britain'',\nthe\n\"Flagship\nis shown on\nthis\ncard.\nEarly\nin\n1950 the\nairline's eighth\nand last 377 had\njoined\nthe fleet which\nlinked New York and Boston with\nEngland,\nScotland and Scandinavia.\nSeptember\n22, 1950\nmarked AOA's last\nflights,\nits\nroutes and aircraft having been sold to\nanother\nair-\nline.\nPhoto courtesy Boeing Commercial Airplane Company\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nN90941 c/n 15957\nB-013\n65838-D\npost card\n2001.082-131"
    ],
